{"word":"συνῳδός","slug":"συνῳδός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>συνῳδός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ᾠδή'><el>ᾠδή</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>singing</i> or <i>sounding in unison with, responsive</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>in harmony, accordant</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>according with, in harmony with</i>, <el>τινί</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}